== 6. d4 ==
White is threatening to win back material by capturing Black's e-pawn. More importantly, they threaten to create dangerous attacks on the e-file while Black is still uncastled. 

Black needs to complete their development, and if possible reinforce the crusading knight on e4. The immediate '''6...d5?''' would leave the c6-knight pinned, allowing the powerful 7. Nxe5!. To get to grips with the situation, Black needs [[/6...b5|'''6...b5''']] to prepare ...d5 by chasing the bishop away.

If Black is unconcerned with opening the e-file, they can accept an extra pawn with [[/6...exd4|'''6...exd4?!''']], the chaotic '''Riga variation''', which leads to a wonderful mess. 

[[/6...Be7|'''6...Be7!?''']] is a semi-useful move. After 7. Re1 this leads to a big liquidation of the centre: 7...b5 8. Rxe4 d5 9. Nxe5 Nxe5 10. Rxe5 bxa4{{Chess/not|+}} and Black can't castle without dropping the e7 bishop. 

